{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"dfa10194-dd3f-411a-84db-5143e2ac8e71","content":"`SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE` was deprecated in Android API 30. In .NET 10 MAUI targeting newer Android APIs, it's no longer honored. The modern fix is to use the **`WindowInsets`** API to detect keyboard (IME) height and apply bottom padding.\n\n**In `Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`:**\n\n```csharp\nusing Android.Views;\nusing AndroidX.Core.View;\n\n[Activity(Theme = \"@style/Maui.SplashTheme\", MainLauncher = true,\n          ConfigurationChanges = /* your existing flags */,\n          WindowSoftInputMode = SoftInput.AdjustNothing)]\npublic class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity\n{\n    protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)\n    {\n        base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);\n\n        var content = FindViewById(Android.Resource.Id.Content)!;\n\n        // Let the view draw behind the keyboard area\n        WindowCompat.SetDecorFitsSystemWindows(Window!, false);\n\n        ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(content, new KeyboardInsetsListener());\n    }\n}\n\nfile class KeyboardInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener\n{\n    public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(Android.Views.View v, WindowInsetsCompat insets)\n    {\n        var ime = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());\n        var bars = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.SystemBars());\n\n        // Use whichever is taller: the keyboard or the nav bar\n        int bottom = Math.Max(ime.Bottom, bars.Bottom);\n        v.SetPadding(v.PaddingLeft, bars.Top, v.PaddingRight, bottom);\n\n        return WindowInsetsCompat.Consumed;\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Why this works:**\n\n| Old approach | New approach |\n|---|---|\n| `AdjustResize` asked the system to shrink your window | `WindowInsets` tells you how tall the keyboard is and you apply padding yourself |\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- `SetDecorFitsSystemWindows(false)` opts into edge-to-edge, which enables IME inset callbacks.\n- The listener fires every time the keyboard opens/closes, so your bottom padding animates with it.\n- On **iOS**, MAUI already adjusts for the keyboard automatically — no extra code needed.\n- If you want smooth keyboard animation, you can additionally use `WindowInsetsAnimationCompat.Callback`, but the above handles the layout shift correctly.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e29ef3ac-22ae-4a62-af73-b13b1f3f17f2","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a .NET MAUI issue with keyboard handling in .NET 10. This is a known behavioral change — `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` was deprecated/removed in Android 11+ and .NET MAUI has been evolving its approach. Let me provide guidance based on what I know.\n\nIn .NET 9, `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` was already deprecated at the Android level (Android 11+), but MAUI had workarounds. In .NET 10, the recommended approach changed.\n\nThe key points:\n1. `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` is deprecated in Android API 30+ (Android 11)\n\n\n2. In .NET 10 / .NET MAUI, the modern approach uses `WindowInsets` APIs and `WindowInsetsCompat` with `ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener` instead of the old resize mode\n3. For .NET MAUI specifically, I need to think through how this translates to the framework's keyboard handling APIs Setting `WindowSoftInputMode` to `AdjustPan` is simpler but shifts the entire view, whereas the more modern approach uses the `WindowInsets` API through platform-specific code or wraps content in a `ScrollView`. For .NET 10 on Android, the cleanest solution is to override `ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener` in the MainActivity to detect keyboard height and adjust the bottom padding accordingly. Writing the listener class...\n\nI should clarify why this became necessary—`SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE` got deprecated in Android API 30, so MAUI's older approach stopped working. The `WindowInsetsCompat` API is the modern replacement that handles both keyboard and system bar insets properly.","outputTokens":1927,"requestId":"3C2D:310F9A:B6286A:E14306:6A012C21"},"id":"10aa832c-edf5-47d9-b659-e206592d69a9","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:09:25.520Z","parentId":"896c3463-b1db-445e-ac9c-beee76e52e3b"}
